author: @roy601912008
comment:
I completed the entire project today and I'm excited to learn more!

I overcame the challenges below and cleared the project:
1. kafka outdated version -> install 3.6.1 instead
2. Java version was also old so I install newer version using this command: sudo yum install java-17-devel
3. Servers run got stuck (Zookeeper and Kafka) -> I rebooted my EC2 server from the AWS EC2 instance console
4. S3 credential issue in KafkaConsumer notebook-> solve it by specifying the access key and secret inside S3FileSystem
5. Got invalid bucket name error (I 'm pretty damn sure the name is legit) when I tried to write to S3 --> it turns out I forgot the ":" in between 's3' and '//' for my s3 bucket path......so be careful of typo

Finally, I was able to achieve the same result at last!! Thank you Darshil for the video!

author: @lhxperimental
comment: The end result you've shown can be achieved using just Python (or any other language) + Postgres. You should explain/justify reasons for choosing the architecture. Athena is not a general purpose query engine, it is expensive to run. So you need to explain why you have used it versus something else and then have a use case that's only possible / simple with this architecture vs something else.  Also what is the real time part? Every database will show saved data after it is inserted.
